            <title>[JDK-8324933] ConcurrentHashTable::statistics_calculate synchronization is expensive</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8324933</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>In the ConcurrentHashTable::statistics_calculate function, we enter and exit a ScopedCS with the global counter for every single bucket. This has showed up to be pretty intense on some machines. We should make the synchronization a bit less intense here.</description>
